subSubSection.paragraph:
The epitheton ‘gertraudae’ is given in fond dedication to Mrs. Gertraud Schoetensack, Hannover (
Germany
).

HABITUS (
Fig. 12 C
). As in female, but smaller (body length from rostral tip to end of FR : 276–312 µm (n = 3) and narrower.

MANDIBLE (
Fig. 15 B
). With slender gnathobase bearing 5 teeth; md palp 1-segmented, with 4 lateral setae and 1 terminal bipinnate seta.

MAXILLULE (
Fig. 15 C
). Praecoxal arthrite with 5 strong bare spines, 2 subapical setae and 2 surface setae. Coxa without spinules, terminally with 1 bare seta. Basis without spinules, terminally with 1 bare and 1 bipinnate seta, laterally with 1 bipinnate seta between basal endite and enp. Exp and enp each represented by 1 bipinnate seta.
